Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.33,0:02:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们撒谎说去割礼会不会不太好\NAre we terrible people for lying and saying that we were going to a bris?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.48,0:02:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 我们又不是坏人\NNo. We're not terrible people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:02:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是需要时间二人世界\NWe need some couple time away from the group.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.51,0:02:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,入了这个网球俱乐部 就只属于咱俩了\NIf we get into this tennis club,it could be our thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.70,0:03:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像"让爱一切成空"只属于空气补给乐队\NLike how making love out of nothing at all is air supply's thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.11,0:03:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,害怕扣篮大赛只属于Lebron\NYeah,like how being terrified of a dunk contest is Lebron's thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.16,0:03:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错\NExactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.66,0:03:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说得对\NYou know,you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.36,0:03:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说谎才能不伤Max的心\NLying is the only way to avoid hurting Max's feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.75,0:03:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不带他玩他承受不来\NDude cannot handle being excluded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.29,0:03:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Max 我们说去墨西哥过周年\NUm,Max,when we said we're going to Mexico for our anniversary...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.69,0:03:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,意思是只有我俩去\NWe meant just us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.90,0:03:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走吧 Danny\NCome on,Danny.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.13,0:03:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想不到最后还是带了他\NI can't believe we brought him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.36,0:03:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想不到他还赢了湿裤大赛\NI can't believe he won that wet pants contest at Se?or O'Callahan's.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.88,0:03:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别担心 去割礼天衣无缝\NDon't worry. A bris is a great lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.81,0:03:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会告诉他我们准备骑马\NI was gonna tell him we were going horseback riding,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.68,0:03:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我担心不小心以后都得用女鞍了\Nbut I was afraid it would come out that I ride sidesaddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.86,0:03:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您好 您好\NShalom. Shalom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.23,0:03:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们好呀 怎么了吗\NHey,guys. What is up?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.08,0:03:42.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们打算跟你们去割礼\NWe were gonna tag along with you guys to that bris.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.79,0:03:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alex从来没去过 我去过两次但忘记了\NAlex has never been to one. And I don't remember my first two.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.92,0:03:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第二次割礼与其说是宗教仪式\NOf course,the second one was less of a religious ceremony
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.11,0:03:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不如说是水上摩托艇惨案\Nand more of a horrific jet skiing accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.51,0:03:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等下 去割礼为啥要穿得像大小威廉姆斯\NWait. Why are you guys going to a bris dressed like Venus and Jane Williams?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.77,0:03:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alex 根本就没什么割礼\NAlex,there is no bris.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.82,0:03:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们是去打网球\NThey're going to play tennis.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.82,0:04:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯一想不通就是你们为何要说谎呢\NThe only question is... why would you lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.51,0:04:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我可没说谎 - 为什么要骗我们\N- Yo,I ain't lie. - Why would you lie to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是我说谎 是情况有变\NThe facts did change,but I ain't lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.52,0:04:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你得说真话 - 别这样跟我说话\N- You need to tell the truth. - Don't come at me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.52,0:04:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你说真话我就不这样 - 别这样跟我说话\N- Wouldn't have to if you told the truth. - Don't come at me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.21,0:04:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你说真话我就不这样 - 你非得这么说是吗\N- I wouldn't have to if you told the truth. - You talk like that,for real?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.66,0:04:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 这是诚信问题 朋友间的互信 - 你让我没有安全感\N- It's about honesty. It's about honesty between friends.- It makes me feel unsafe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.09,0:04:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了好了 被你们发现了\NAll right,okay. We're busted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.79,0:04:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要去一个私人网球俱乐部\NBrad and I are joining a private tennis club,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.79,0:04:22.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们没说是因为不清楚你们的态度\Nand we didn't tell you because we-- we know how you get,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.10,0:04:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怕你们知道会取笑我们 懂吗\N- and we were afraid that you-- - That you would,um,make fun of us. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.70,0:04:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怕被你们笑\NYes. Make fun of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.33,0:04:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就怕这个 怕被你们取笑\NThat... was the fear. That was the fear right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.25,0:04:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托 这就是我\NGuys,come on. This is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.07,0:04:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我当然会笑你们\NOf course I'm gonna make fun of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.00,0:04:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现编现卖 哥就擅长这个\NI mean,almost immediately,I'm in an area of what time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.26,0:04:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您的怀表几点啦 土豪大使\Nis your monocle fitting, Ambassador Goldface Von Cash?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.83,0:04:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 别说了 - 这只是个暖场\N- Stop. - And that's just first blurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.63,0:04:46.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 点个赞 - 不邀请你们实在说不过去\N- Love it. - Guys,we would've totally invited you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.13,0:04:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这个俱乐部真的很挫\Nbut it's gonna be really lame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.69,0:04:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们自己都不太想去\NI mean,we don't even wanna do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.02,0:04:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是Brad需要发展下人脉\NIt's really just a networking thing for Brad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.27,0:04:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肯定不适合你\NDefinitely not your scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.27,0:04:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 停 听不下去了 - 就是\N- Say no more. That sounds horrible. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.27,0:04:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 结束了找你 如果没被球砸死的话\NAgreed. Hey,catch you after,if we haven't killed ourselves. Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.23,0:05:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 别这样 - 好了 世界和平\N- No. Don't do that. - Okay,all right. Peace on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.05,0:05:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好好打球吧 土豪大使\NEnjoy your tennis,Ambassador Goldface.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.83,0:05:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也是 土豪夫人\NYou,too,Mrs. Cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.56,0:05:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是太搞笑了\NOh. That's so,so funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.19,0:05:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我的天 - 我想他们信了\N- Good save. - I think they bought it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.25,0:05:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们绝对以为我们信了\NI bet they think we bought it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.66,0:05:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不适合我们也说得出来 你懂的\NNot our scene? You know what that means,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.33,0:05:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那俩暴发户觉得我们不够格参加俱乐部\NThose two richies think we're not good enough to hang out at a tennis club.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.75,0:05:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 他们真的这么想吗 - 那是\N- They do? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.03,0:05:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是朋友渐行渐远的原因 Alex\NThis is how groups of friends fall apart,Alex.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.27,0:05:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不久他们就开始过上流生活\NPretty soon they're gonna start doing all this rich people stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.53,0:05:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,留下我们这些穷人自己一边玩\Nand leave us poor folks to fend for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.62,0:05:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们得做点什么 - 对\N- We need to do something about it. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.83,0:05:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让上等人看看底层人民也不差\NLet's show that 1% that the other 10% are just as good as they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.24,0:05:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是\NExactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.85,0:05:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全家出游真开心\NWhat a fun family outing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.00,0:05:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 好开心 - 就是 真好玩\N- Oh,what fun. - I know. It's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.53,0:05:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从Crispin Glover借来的原版的机器娃娃\NThey got the original "Small Wonder" robot on loan from Crispin Glover.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.04,0:05:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,慢着 收集机器人的机器人 我说对了吗\NWait. Robots collecting robots. Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.75,0:05:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人要喝饮料吗\NCan I get anyone a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.32,0:05:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我车里有家酿雪梨酒 我去拿\NI have a lovely homemade pear wine in the trunk of my car. Let me get that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.36,0:05:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不如来点香槟\NWell,uh,actually,how about some champagne?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.44,0:05:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们有点事想说\NBecause we do have some news.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.11,0:05:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就知道 他们要结婚了\NI knew it. They're getting married.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.81,0:06:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我...去死好了\NI... die.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.13,0:06:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如你们所知 我们都很爱对方\NAs you know,Big David and I care about each other very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.25,0:06:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后呢\NAnd?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.31,0:06:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们年纪也不小了 - 老了\N- And we're not getting any younger. - We're a little old.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.15,0:06:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后呢\NAnd?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.61,0:06:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们准备领养个小孩\NWe're adopting a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.42,0:06:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 啊哦 - 呃\N- Oops. - Uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.96,0:06:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看来你俩有点被吓到\NI can see that you kids are a teeny bit wigged out,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.70,0:06:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这么说吧 养育你们的过程很幸福\Nbut listen,we got so much joy out of raising you both,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.76,0:06:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们打算一起再感受这幸福\Nthat we've decided to do it again... together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.14,0:06:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且你们也长大独立了\NBesides,we're through raising you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.99,0:06:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你们大了 也不需要我们了 - 是的\N- You're all grown up. Don't need us anymore.- Oh,yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.93,0:06:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不需要我们了\NIt's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.12,0:06:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以 你们觉得怎样\NSo... what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.05,0:06:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们觉得怎样?\NWhat do we think?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.63,0:06:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,简直太棒了\NThis is great news.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.55,0:06:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们喜欢哪种? 非裔 亚裔 还是白人小孩?\NWhat flavor are you thinking? Black,Ayzsh,original recipe?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.05,0:06:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dave 你想对这劲爆的消息 说点什么吗?\NDave,you wanna weigh in on this breaking news?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.27,0:06:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道 外表上我看起来是名 禁欲主义"纯基佬"\Nwell,I know on the outside I may look like a stoic "Just For Men" box model,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.70,0:06:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是内心里我是很"爵士范儿"的\Nbut on the inside,I'm jazzed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.70,0:06:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"爵士范儿" 这词儿再合适不过了\NJazzed. That is the perfect word.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.99,0:06:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,表达了我们的激动之情的同时 还提到了爵士\NIt encapsulates our excitement while simultaneously referencing jazz,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.31,0:07:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国的一种纯正艺术形式\NAmerica's one true art form.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.20,0:07:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以 恭喜\NSo,yeah. Congrats.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.35,0:07:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 谢谢 - 或者 说的更准确一些...\N- Thank you. - Or,more purely stated...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.78,0:07:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这沙冰太棒了 Chad\NGood on ya,Chad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.36,0:07:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是你的手艺 兄弟\NLike your style,buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.44,0:07:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 宝贝? - 嗯\N- Babe? - Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.54,0:07:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这地方棒极了 特别是更衣间\NThis place is amazing, especially the locker room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.84,0:07:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是说 刮胡膏? 爱死了 毛巾? 爱死了\NI mean,shaving cream? Heated. Towels? Heated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.57,0:07:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更衣间的服务员? 更加爱死了...\NLocker room attendant? Heated...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.83,0:07:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我告诉他那些洗涤液里满是 有毒的对羟苯甲酸酯\NWhen I pointed out all of those lotions are full of toxic parabens,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.32,0:07:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别担心 我告诉他了防治办法\Nbut don't worry. I gave him a thick tip.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.40,0:07:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恩 我猜到了\NMm,bet you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我刚刚吃了杯石榴蓝莓藜麦沙冰\NWell,I just had a pomegranate blueberry quinoa smoothie,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.89,0:07:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我告诉你 如果有一点儿氧化物留在我体内\Nand let me tell you,if there is one single oxidant left up in me,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.27,0:07:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会变成猴子他叔\NI am a monkey's uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.97,0:07:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 老天 真希望他们让我加入 - 我也是\N- God,I hope they let us join. - Oh,me,too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.15,0:07:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brad Jane? 我是Connie Kelly 会员主管\NBrad,Jane? Connie Kelly,Membership Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.56,0:07:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都说 永远别相信说话用俩人名开头的人\NI know what they say. Never trust a man with two first names,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.90,0:07:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果是女士们的名字 这句话就不算数了\Nbut when it's ladies' names,it doesn't apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.20,0:07:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 噢! - 噢 Connie\N- Oh! - Oh,Connie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.67,0:07:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欢迎来到黄金海岸网球俱乐部\NWelcome to the Gold Coast Tennis Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.99,0:07:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们很兴奋能够来到这儿 Connie.\NWe are excited to be here,Connie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.37,0:08:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也很激动能向你们展示这里\NOh,and I'm excited to show you around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.00,0:08:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再等等另外两位\NUh,just waiting on two others.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.49,0:08:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢! 他们过来了\NAnd oh! There they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.10,0:08:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 嗨! - 你好!\N- Hello! - Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.45,0:08:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brad Jane 这两位是 Max和Alex.\NBrad,Jane,this is Max and Alex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.70,0:08:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 一个打网球的好天气 不是吗? - 的确\N- Lovely day for tennising,isn't it? - Oh,it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.06,0:08:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们能开始了吗? - 好的\N- Shall we begin? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.14,0:08:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 快点吧 - 等不及了\N- Oh,we shall. - Oh,we shall.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.50,0:08:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以 我们的父母要一起收养一个孩子\NSo our parents are adopting a baby together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.25,0:08:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不敢相信我不再是他们的宝贝了\NI can't believe I'm not gonna be the baby anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.67,0:08:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这绝对是我现在最可怕的噩梦\NThis is now officially my worst nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.00,0:08:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错 比跟Jason Giambi 做爱的梦还要可怕\NThat's right,Jason Giambi sex dream. You're out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.05,0:08:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们都这岁数了 不该再收养孩子\NI mean,they shouldn't be adopting a baby at their age.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.34,0:08:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们应该腌制葡萄柚 看广播电视\NThey should be salting their grapefruit and watching broadcast television.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.36,0:08:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道这还意味着什么吗?\NAnd you know what this means?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.68,0:08:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们将来要抚养这个孩子\NWe're the ones who are gonna have to take care of this kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.07,0:08:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我才30 一个30岁的人 怎么能照顾孩子\NI'm 30. How is a 30-year-old supposed to take care of a baby?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.00,0:08:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,严格的说 你已经31了\NWell,you're 31 if you're a minute,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.57,0:08:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 但谁在乎呢? - 好伤人\N- but who's counting? - Hurtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.94,0:08:48.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,认真的 我们应该怎么办?\NBut seriously,what are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.69,0:08:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是个坏主意 他们没有用 长远的眼光来看待这个问题\NThis is a bad idea. They aren't thinking long-term.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.31,0:08:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们忘了抚养一个孩子不只是陪 他/她玩耍和抱抱\NThey're forgetting that having a kid isn't all tickles and hugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.98,0:08:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很确定如果他们照顾一天孩子 他们肯定会表现得像...\NYeah,I'm sure if they had to take care of a baby for just one day,they'd be like...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.33,0:09:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要孩子 谢谢\Nno,thanks,baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.72,0:09:03.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错\NMmm,exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.27,0:09:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等等 我们需要做的只是询问\NWait. And all we have to do is ask
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.71,0:09:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的朋友能否帮照顾 他们的孩子几天\None of our friends with a kid if we can babysit,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.10,0:09:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们将孩子推到爸妈家\Nthen we bring that stroller meat around Big Dave and Dana
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.79,0:09:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提醒他们带孩子是多可怕的一件事情\Nand remind them that having a kid is a nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.66,0:09:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好主意 把他们吓退缩\NGood idea. Scare 'em straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.56,0:09:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像我们把Max带到监狱吓他那次一样\NLike that time we took Max to that prison and scared
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.89,0:09:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有犯人住在一起\Nall those inmates into getting their lives together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.77,0:09:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 这是真爱 - 就这么定了\N- Tough love. - Let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.54,0:09:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这儿就是宏伟的中央球场\NAnd here is the grand dame herself-- center court.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.58,0:09:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果这场地会说话 它一定会说 "为什么上帝要这么对我?\NMan,if this court could talk, it would say,"Why has God done this to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.44,0:09:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,诅咒你 上帝!"\NCurses to you,God!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.94,0:09:39.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Connie 你太搞笑了\NConnie,you are a treat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.84,0:09:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请原谅 稍等我几分钟\NExcuse me for just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.04,0:09:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是故意装作跟他很熟\NUh,don't wanna be a name dropper,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.09,0:09:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我想我刚看到了库克郡的 副审计官Sheryl Pflimf.\Nbut I think I just spotted Cook County Deputy Comptroller Sheryl Pflimf.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.80,0:09:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们关心很好 等我过去跟他打个招呼\NWe're dear friends. One moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.89,0:09:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheryl!\NSheryl!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.07,0:09:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you guys doing here你们在这儿干嘛\NWhat the hell are you guys doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.51,0:09:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,旅游散心 考虑加入俱乐部 面对现实吧\NTaking a tour,thinking about joining the club. Sussin' it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.48,0:09:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 没错 直面现实 - 直面什么?\N- Yeah,straight sussin'. - Straight what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.05,0:09:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,得了吧 你们才不是真想加入 一个网球俱乐部\NCome on. You guys don't wanna join a tennis club.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.90,0:10:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么? 因为我们打不好网球?\NWhy? 'Cause it's not our scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.40,0:10:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不能成功的挥动球拍\NYou don't think we're good enough to rub elbows
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.40,0:10:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像你和Sheryl Pflimfs一样？\Nwith you and the Sheryl Pflimfs of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.40,0:10:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说这儿跟我俩再合适不过\NWell,I say we fit in here just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.10,0:10:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你? 跟这儿合适?\NReally? You fit in?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.59,0:10:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Alex 你问了三个人有没有灰色娃娃 - 没错\N- Alex,you've asked three people if they have any Grey Poupon.- Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.55,0:10:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Max 你看起来就像John McEnroe 的胖堂兄-John Mac奶酪\NAnd,Max,you look like John McEnroe's fat cousin, John Mac-n-Cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.48,0:10:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Max 能否麻烦你们在毁了我们 享受这里之前离开?\NMax,can you just get outta here before you ruin this for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.84,0:10:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你们才应该在毁了我们的旅途前离开 - 没错\N- You get outta here before you ruin this for us.- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.77,0:10:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我回来了 - 太好了!\N- Sorry. - Ohh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.60,0:10:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheryl太能说了\NSheryl was a real yapper.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.93,0:10:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她唯一管不住的就是她的嘴\NThe only thing she can't deputy comptrol is her mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.94,0:10:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女人都很能说\NWomen be talkin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.40,0:10:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,话说回来 我想你们都忍不住想 试试在这场地打球了吧?\NAnywho,I'm sure you all are probably itching to try out the courts,huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.44,0:10:35.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们何不来场双打呢?\NWhy don't you guys play doubles?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.93,0:10:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我不认为这是个好主意 - Connie! Brad 我们能打双打!\N- Um,I don't think so. - Connie! Brad,we can play doubles!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.28,0:10:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没问题 我给你们安排下场地\NSure. I'll go set up a court for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.88,0:10:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我觉得... - 太好了\N- You know... - Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.20,0:10:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 规则如下\NOkay. Here's the deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.08,0:10:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你们赢了 我们将永不 踏入这片场地\NIf you guys win,we'll never step foot in this place again,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.60,0:10:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果我们赢了 我们有权利选择加入这儿\Nbut if we win,then we get the choice of joining up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.13,0:10:51.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们可能就是适合俱乐部的人\NWe just might be club people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.36,0:10:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Max 没人通过网球比赛做决定 兄弟\NMax,nobody solves things through tennis matches anymore,bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.79,0:10:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们又不在80年代 - 你害怕了 Arthur Ashey?\N- It's not the '80s. - You scared,Arthur Ashe-y?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.01,0:11:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人能叫我 Ashy... 永远没有!\NNobody calls me Ashy... ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.40,0:11:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不是打了我完美无瑕的脸一耳光\NThat is not just a slap in my evenly moisturized face.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.41,0:11:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是对我的洗涤顾问和我的面霜的侮辱!\NIt's an insult to my personal lotion consultant and my creamist!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.84,0:11:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 比赛就比赛! - 谁怕谁\N- It's on! - Oh,it is on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.36,0:11:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 谁怕谁 - 谁怕谁\N- Oh,it is on. - Oh,it is on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.22,0:11:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧... 我问过了所有人 没人愿意给我们孩子\NWelp... no one would give me a kid, and I asked everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.61,0:11:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿! Allison\NHey! Allison.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.77,0:11:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还记得你曾吓了我五分钟说 这孩子是我的吗?\NRemember when you thought that baby was mine for,like,five minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.86,0:11:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得我可以借着孩子五分钟吗?\NDo you think I could borrow it for,like,five minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.44,0:11:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也生不出一个来\NI couldn't get one either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.78,0:11:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我被拒绝了太多次 我感觉就像是 Jason Giambi性梦里的Jason Giambi\NI got so many "no's," I felt like Jason Giambi in my Jason Giambi sex dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.71,0:11:42.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,家长什么时候变得这么黏 他们的孩子了?\NWhen did parents become so attached to their kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.18,0:11:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你爱某种东西 就应该给它自由\NIf you love something,set it free.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.17,0:11:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或者借给你楼下的邻居\NOr lend it to your downstairs neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.08,0:11:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能借到一把沙龙级别带烘干机的椅子\NYou're telling me I can rent a salon-grade hooded dryer chair,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.55,0:11:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却借不到一个孩子？\Nbut I can't rent a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.65,0:11:53.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等等 David 你可能提示了我什么\NWait,David. You may just be on to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.27,0:11:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.27,0:11:57.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么在家能做的时候要去 闷热的沙龙呢?\NWhy do in a stuffy salon what you can do in the comfort of your own home?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.21,0:11:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 我是说你能借到一个宝宝\NNo. You can rent a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.56,0:12:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的公关公司一直在付费请 宝宝拍广告\NMy PR firm casts babies in commercials all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.76,0:12:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我打一个假的拍摄电话\NIf I put out a fake casting call,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.84,0:12:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能找到50个疯狂妈妈\NI could get 50 crazy stage moms
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.20,0:12:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 十分钟内他们的孩子就会在我 办公室门口排队 - 真的吗?\N- and their kids lined up in my office in ten minutes.- Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.70,0:12:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,永远别低估一颗妈妈为孩子 攒大学学费的心\NNever underestimate the lure of building your child a college fund
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.92,0:12:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还能随时用来给你的男友Tico 买一辆ATV\Nwhich you can then raid to buy an ATV for your boyfriend Tico.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.79,0:12:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可悲呀可悲\NSad but sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.09,0:12:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就说吧\NTold ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.16,0:12:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,干得好\NGood job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.53,0:12:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就像是一个真的拍摄需求\NThis feels like a real casting call.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.86,0:12:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过我很关心等待间的食物短缺问题\NAlthough I am concerned with the waiting room food situation or lack thereof.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.92,0:12:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道我们午餐在节食\NNow I know we're butting up against lunch,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.56,0:12:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但也许你能摆放一个零食碟子\Nbut maybe you could get a mezze plate going
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.46,0:12:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放一些葡萄 或者鹰嘴豆泥\Nwith some grape leaves,maybe some hummus.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.39,0:12:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么? Dave 我们没有时间\NWhat? Dave,there is no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.21,0:12:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们只需要找到这儿最糟糕的妈妈\NWe just need to find the worst mother here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.95,0:12:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及最不听话的宝宝交给我们的父母\Nand the most rotten,miserable baby and dump it on our parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.04,0:12:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢 太棒了\NJackpot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.92,0:12:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你确定吗?\NAre you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.12,0:12:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们简直太完美了 开始吧\NThey're perfect. Just play along.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.18,0:12:53.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家好 Penny Hartz 公关专员\NHello. Penny Hartz,PR.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.30,0:12:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dave Rose 产品设计 主要负责两栖鞋类\NDave Rose,PD. Product Design. Amphibious footwear,mostly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.11,0:12:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 不过我们可以晚点再说这个 - 他是我们的客户\N- But that can all come later. - Okay,he's the client.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.47,0:13:00.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁是我们这位漂亮宝宝啊?\NNow who is this precious child?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.93,0:13:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 他叫Eddie 不好意思 他有点累坏了\NOh,this is Eddie. I'm so sorry. He's a little tuckered out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.78,0:13:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管累没累坏 我们认为小Eddie 就是我们的正确拍摄人选\NTuckered out or not, we think Little Eddie's the right man for the part.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.71,0:13:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 真的吗? - 我们只需要带他去隔壁房间 做个试镜\N- Really? - We just need to take him into the next room for a screen test
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.78,0:13:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不在意在这儿稍等的吧?\Nif you don't mind hanging out here in the waiting area.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.95,0:13:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,实在抱歉 我们时间太紧 没来得及准备个零食碟子\NI apologize ahead of time for the lack of a mezze plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.72,0:13:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们几小时后带他回来 没问题吧?\NOkay. And we'll bring him back in a couple hours. That be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.21,0:13:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不敢相信他被选上了 我的给他爸爸打个电话!\NI can't believe he booked it. I have to call his dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.80,0:13:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,得经过他的同意 这是监护协议的一部分\NTo ask permission. It's part of our custody agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.13,0:13:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我确定会没问题的 我不想打断他 他在他的毕业舞会上\NI'm sure it's fine. I don't wanna bug him. He's at his prom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.94,0:13:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宝贝 你听到没? 你是个明星\NYou hear that,baby? You're a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.38,0:13:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是明星\NWe're stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.14,0:13:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 是的! - 没错!\N- Yeah! - Yes! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.30,0:14:57.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,击垮你们!\N...destroyed you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.86,0:15:01.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们赢了! - 我们把你们打得...\N- We won! - We won your...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.64,0:15:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们 赢了!\NWe ...destroyed you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.59,0:15:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,屎去吧\NWhoopsie daisy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.94,0:15:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不配拿这个\NYou don't deserve this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.37,0:15:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 亲爱的 - 干嘛\N- Honey... - What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.23,0:15:21.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了\NWhat's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.36,0:15:27.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除非我们不想加入这家超酷的俱乐部\N...is how we would have celebrated
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.43,0:15:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们才会这么庆祝\Nif we didn't wanna belong to this awesome club.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.02,0:15:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道 这计划有点疯狂\NI don't know. This plan is kinda crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.02,0:15:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,基本上我们算是绑架了个孩子\NWe're basically kidnapping a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.02,0:15:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道办不办得到\NI'm not sure I can go through with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.40,0:15:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 没错 是疯狂了点\NOkay,yes,it is crazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.33,0:15:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但怎么比得上老爸老妈在这岁数 收养孩子来得要命\Nbut is it any crazier than our parents adopting a baby at their age?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.61,0:15:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错 值得一试\NYou're right. I guess the juice is worth the squeeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.12,0:15:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且 我们也会在一小时内还回来\NBesides,we're gonna be back in an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.00,0:15:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还有什么好担心的\NWhat you should be worrying about is that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.87,0:15:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,五分钟后 我们就会和爸妈一起吃午饭\Nwe're meeting our parents for lunch in five minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.87,0:15:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而操心Eddie刚突然变身成超萌Eddie\Nand Fussy Eddie here has suddenly decided to turn into Super Sweet Eddie
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.96,0:15:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不会让他们打退堂鼓\Nwho won't bum them out at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.29,0:16:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝啊 他真是超萌的\NMy God. You're right. He is being super sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.44,0:16:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 真想有个像你这样的小弟弟 - 什么\N- I wish I had a little brother just like you.- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.18,0:16:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 对了这完全违背我们的初衷\NOh,right,that's the exact opposite of what we're trying to do here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.86,0:16:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了 我们只要把他弄哭就行了 对吧\NOkay,so I guess we just need to make it cry,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.94,0:16:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们该怎么做\NHow do we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.51,0:16:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喂 喂\NHey,hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.25,0:16:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我哭怎么样 那他就会哭 对吧\NWhat if I start crying? That'll make it cry,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.63,0:16:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想怎么把自己弄哭\NHow are you gonna make yourself cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.00,0:16:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我这人生还有什么意思\NWhat am I doing with my life?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.16,0:16:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连我妈谈的恋爱都比我的好\NMy mom's in a better relationship than I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.30,0:16:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而我还喷着Shania Twain的香水 (加拿大著名乡村女歌手)\NAnd I'm wearing a perfume by Shania Twain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.08,0:16:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喔 还真快\NWow,that was fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.40,0:16:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些都已经录好了 你只需要按个开始键\NIt's all cued up. You just sorta have to press "Play."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.66,0:16:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该死的 没用\NDamn it. It's not working.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.21,0:16:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我骂骂他怎样\NWhat if I insult it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.30,0:16:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿 小屁孩 只会靠乳房吃饭 你个小傻子\Nhey,baby. Way to get all your meals from a boob, you tiny moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.50,0:16:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他听不懂的\NHe doesn't understand words.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.99,0:16:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你得说得更凶残点\NYou're gonna have to use a harsher tone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.42,0:16:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,记住我的脸\NRemember my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.59,0:16:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 你可能办不到\NOh,you probably can't,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.96,0:16:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你还没有物体恒存性意识 你个秃头傻帽\Nbecause you don't have object permanence, you bald bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.26,0:16:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是怎么回事\NWhat the hell is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.86,0:16:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,问得好 Trish 聪明\NGood question,Trish. Smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.08,0:16:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我刚模仿恶魔在跟小Eddie讲话\NI was just speaking to Little Eddie in a demon voice
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.41,0:16:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看他对广告拍摄时的吵闹忙乱有何反应\Nto see how he'd react to the hustle and bustle of a commercial shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.54,0:16:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而小Eddie的表现让我感动地都哭了\NAnd I was crying because Little Eddie's performance moved me to tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.93,0:17:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等等 先说你们到这下面来干嘛\NWait. What are you doing down here in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.89,0:17:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那先说你到这下面来干嘛 Trish\NWhat are you doing down here in the first place,Trish?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.33,0:17:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等候室没吃的了 而我饿了\NThere was no food in the waiting room, and I got hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.92,0:17:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 早就说了 - 说真的 你们打算把我孩子带去哪里吗\N- Told ya. - Seriously,were you taking my baby someplace?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.98,0:17:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 什么 没有 - 那太疯狂了\N- What? No. - That's crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.33,0:17:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿 准备走了吗 的士已经等在外面了\NHey,y'all! Ready to split? Cab's waiting outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.79,0:17:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 这就是你们说的小惊喜吗\NOhh. Is this the little surprise you told us about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.03,0:17:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多可爱的小宝宝啊\NWhat a perfect little baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.41,0:17:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许我们就该偷这个 我说的是对啊还是对啊\NMaybe we should just steal this one, am I right or am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.20,0:17:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你就跟我回家吧\NYou are coming home with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.55,0:17:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要叫警察了\NI'm calling the cops.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.13,0:17:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trish\NTrish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.76,0:17:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以你和Dave绑架了这个妈妈的孩子\NSo you and Dave kidnapped this woman's baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.06,0:17:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小Dave 是真的吗\NSmall Dave,is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.57,0:17:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这取决于你怎么定义“真的”了\NIt depends how you define "true."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.83,0:17:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果是指发生的事情 那是的\NIf you mean the thing that happened,then yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.24,0:17:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这已经超越底限了\NThis is beyond unacceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.64,0:17:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们究竟为什么要怎么做\NWhy in the world would you do something like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.94,0:17:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来证明你和老Dave有多不靠谱\NUm,to prove how irresponsible you and Big Dave are being,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.76,0:17:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望你们已经吸取教训了\Nand I hope you learned your lesson and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.34,0:17:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提醒下 不是你们教育我们 而是我们在教育你们\NFYI-- you don't teach us lessons. We teach you lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.40,0:17:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不管是谁教谁什么\NI don't care who is teaching what to who.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.40,0:18:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还是要叫警察\NIt doesn't change the fact that I'm calling the cops.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.81,0:18:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了 女士 可以的话\NAll right,ma'am,if I may,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.14,0:18:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想我了解情况了\NI think I know what's happening here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.79,0:18:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我女朋友和我想领养个孩子\NMy girlfriend and I wanted to adopt a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.12,0:18:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我梳理下\NLet me back up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.16,0:18:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是他的爸爸\NI am his father,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.98,0:18:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后我曾跟这位小姐的妈妈约会\Nand I've been dating this young lady's mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.11,0:18:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我再补充下 那是在1980年\NLet me back up again. The year was 1980.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.86,0:18:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还是个风流倜傥 风华正茂的骚年\NI was a sexually active young buck with some notions
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.49,0:18:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,认为避孕是完全错误的\Nabout birth control that were dead wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.75,0:18:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了 他是想说我们想领养个孩子\NOkay,I think what he's trying to say is that we're adopting a baby,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.76,0:18:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而我们的老大们反应强烈\Nand our older children are freaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.69,0:18:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 这我能理解\NOkay,that I get.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.31,0:18:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我有Eddie时 我那八岁的孩子完全暴走了\NYou know when I had Eddie here, my 8-year-old totally acted out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.59,0:18:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,显然 她是真的理解\NClearly,this one gets it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.47,0:18:34.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以 妈妈们有共同语言\NSo,mama grizzly to mama grizzly,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.94,0:18:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们放这些愣头青一马 怎样\Nwhat do you say we give these cubs a pass,huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.96,0:18:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是说 他们还只是孩子\NI mean,they're just kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.49,0:18:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,呃 他们无疑有三十岁了 所以不行\NUm... they're easily 30,so no.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.88,0:18:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 31 - 好吧\N- 31. - All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.02,0:18:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得像个爸爸那样来处理这事\NWell,I'm gonna have to handle this like a dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.21,0:18:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 开始了 - 够了说一声 Trish\N- Here we go. - Say when,Trish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.00,0:18:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我正在存钱买沙滩车 所以\NI am saving for an ATV,so...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.41,0:18:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,新的还是二手的\NNew or used?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.66,0:18:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 新的 - 好吧\N- New. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.34,0:18:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放进我的钱包\NPut it in my purse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.00,0:18:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,收据发邮件给我吧\NE-mail me the receipt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.44,0:19:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么 我猜你们没能加入这间俱乐部\NSo... I guess you guys didn't get into the club.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.86,0:19:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\NNo,we didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.88,0:19:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道都是我的错 我很抱歉 我只是\NIt's my fault. I know. I'm sorry. It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.88,0:19:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我陷入妄想 你们会奋发向上\NI got all paranoid that you guys would move on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.09,0:19:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后开始过上流生活 我就再也见不到你们了\Nand start doing rich stuff,and I'd never see you guys again
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.62,0:19:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你们会参加像 电影大开眼界里的各种派对\N'cause you'd be going all "Eyes Wide Shut" parties
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.76,0:19:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后和Tommy Hilfiger比赛泡妞 (休闲服装品牌创始人)\Nand hunting people for sport with Tommy Hilfiger
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.10,0:19:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或其他上流社会会做的什么事\Nor whatever rich people supposedly do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.71,0:19:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Max 这跟上流生活无关 好吗\NMax,it's not about rich stuff,all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.13,0:19:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这甚至也无关网球\NIt's not even about tennis.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.78,0:19:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是Jane和我想过些二人生活\NIt's about Jane and I having something to do just for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.25,0:19:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们很喜欢跟你们一起打发时间\NLook,we love hanging out with you guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.09,0:19:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们也需要一些情侣专属时间\Nbut we need some couple time to ourselves,too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.54,0:19:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢 那你们怎么不早说\NWell,why didn't you just say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.96,0:19:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不想让你难过\NWe didn't wanna hurt your feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.46,0:19:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且每当有谁想干点啥不带上你\Nand you sort of freak out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.21,0:19:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你都有点行为怪异 - 不 我才没有\N- whenever anyone tries to do something without you.- No,I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.79,0:19:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,呃 还记得Dave患阑尾炎时吗\NUh,remember when Dave had appendicitis?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.34,0:19:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你揍自己胃部也想患一个\NAnd you punched yourself in the stomach so you could get it,too,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.18,0:19:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,结果却得了痢疾\Nbut all you got was red diarrhea?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.77,0:19:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道了 你们有理\NPoint taken. Advantage-- you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.77,0:19:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的 我很抱歉\NLook,seriously,I'm sorry,for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.87,0:19:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也很抱歉\NI'm sorry,too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.13,0:19:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.64,0:19:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么 我们走吧\NLet's just go,though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.57,0:19:53.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪儿也别去\NYou're not going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.22,0:19:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想到一个绝妙的主意 能让你们加入这家俱乐部\NI've got the perfect plan to get you back into this club.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.24,0:19:57.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想没必要了\NI don't think it's necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.65,0:19:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么 他想做什么\NWhat? What is he up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.77,0:20:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知道 他都跳着走了\NI don't know. He's got some pep in his step.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.08,0:20:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 没错 他看起来好兴奋 - 他会扭转局面的\N- Yes,he seemed very excited. - He's gonna turn it around.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.48,0:20:05.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我想是的 - 不 不要吧 我们又不一定要加入它\N- I think he is.- No,no, let's not. I don't think we need to go that far with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.39,0:20:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没起作用 没起作用\NIt didn't work! It didn't work! It didn't work! It didn't work!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.63,0:20:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的主意到底是什么\NWhat exactly was his plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.52,0:20:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没起作用\NIt didn't work!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.28,0:20:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以 Dave和我很抱歉\NSo,listen,Dave and I are so sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.89,0:20:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们做了傻事 还对你们收养的事大惊小怪\Nwe acted like idiots and freaked out about you guys adopting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.79,0:20:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老实说 这不同寻常\NAnd honestly,it's unorthodox,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.44,0:20:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果有谁能做的话 就只有你们\Nbut if anyone can make it work,it's you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.74,0:20:29.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们会成为好父母 因为你们本来就是\NYou'll be great parents because you are great parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.33,0:20:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 最好的 - 听你们这么说真是贴心\N- The best. - That's mighty sweet of you kids to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.02,0:20:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是 现在谁也别想让我们收养孩子\Nbut,um,there is no way in hell we're adopting a kid now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.43,0:20:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,休想 除非我死了\NNo! Not on my watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.35,0:20:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,逃过一劫\NDodged a bullet on that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.35,0:20:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 对吗 爸爸 - 是的 长官\N- Right,papa? - Yes,sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.62,0:20:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以在大厅看到小Eddie\NSo seeing Little Eddie in the lobby
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.77,0:20:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提醒了你们养大个孩子有多难\Nactually reminded you guys how hard it is to raise kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.34,0:20:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 事实上在大厅看到你们两个 想偷走小Eddie\NNo,actually seeing you two in the lobby trying to steal Little Eddie
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.05,0:20:55.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提醒了我们要有个孩子有多难\Nreminded us how hard it is to have kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.35,0:20:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错 而显然 我们还没有 将你们两个蠢蛋养育成人\NYeah,and clearly we are not finished raising you two dumbasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.48,0:21:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老David和我真正想说的是\NI think what Big David and I are really trying to say is that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.36,0:21:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们两个永远是我们的小宝贝\Nyou two will always be our babies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.61,0:21:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那梳梳我的头发 给我做Penny牌巧克力碎片蛋糕\NThen brush my hair and make me chocolate chip Penny-cakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.29,0:21:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,挠挠我的背 直到我咕噜咕噜叫\NAnd tickle my back until I coo and coo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.66,0:21:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 给最最漂亮的公主梳梳头发 - 挠挠你的胃 好不好\N- Brush the hair of a beautiful, beautiful princess. - Tickle your tummy,huh?
